  "summary": "Bed is Occupied after pc shut off",
  "environment_raw": null,
  "description": "I went to sleep in my bed in-game when my power temporarily went out. After regaining power, I re-logged into my world, which saved to right before I slept. When I tried sleeping in the bed, it said the bed was occupied, even though it was a single player world. Breaking the bed did reset it back to its normal state. n n",
  "Steps to Reproduce": "1. Create a new single-player world in Minecraft with default settings.\n2. Locate or craft a bed and place it in a safe area.\n3. Ensure it is night time in the game (between 12542 and 23459 ticks) or during a thunderstorm.\n4. Right-click on the bed to sleep in it, allowing the screen to fade to black.\n5. Simulate a power outage by shutting down your computer or disconnecting power.\n6. After a few moments, restore power and restart your computer.\n7. Launch Minecraft and re-enter the same single-player world.\n8. Wait for the game to load, which should revert to the state just before you slept.\n9. Approach the bed and attempt to right-click on it to sleep again.\n10. Observe the message indicating the bed is occupied, despite being the only player in the world.\n11. Break the bed and note that it resets to its normal state, allowing you to sleep again.",
  "Environment": "Minecraft Java Edition Version 1.21.8",
  "Observed Behavior": "After the player sleeps in a bed in a single-player world and experiences a power outage, upon re-logging into the game, the bed is marked as \"occupied.\" This occurs despite the game saving the state prior to the player sleeping, effectively preventing the player from using the bed again. The message displayed when attempting to sleep is \"This bed is occupied.\" The only way to resolve this issue is to break the bed, which resets its state and allows the player to sleep in it again. This behavior does not align with the expected functionality of beds in single-player mode, where a bed should not remain occupied after a player has logged out and back in, especially if the game state was saved before the player went to sleep.",
  "Expected Behavior": "When a player sleeps in a bed in a single-player world, the game should properly register the sleep state and allow the player to sleep again upon re-logging into the world. If the power goes out and the game saves before the player sleeps, the bed should not be marked as occupied when the player logs back in. Instead, the player should be able to use the bed again without any issues. If the bed is functioning correctly, the player should receive no error messages, and the game should allow them to sleep immediately, advancing the time to dawn. If the bed is broken, it should reset to its normal state, allowing the player to place it again and sleep without encountering the \"bed is occupied\" message.",
